  "text": "Reaction times (RTs) for hits (in ms) and task accuracy (correct response rate in %) on the IDT were analyzed using a three (reward: NR vs. SR . This indicates that incentive manipulations within the experimental task were successful. Post hoc contrasts for accuracy revealed the highest the correct response rate for SR, the lowest the correct response rate for IR and the NR condition intermediate (all ps < 0.004, all Cohen's ds > 0.77) (see Table 2 ). Although we intended to maintain an equal average accuracy across conditions and participants by adjusting the target duration according to individual trial-by-trial performance, our finding of different accuracy rates for the three incentive conditions is in line with prior studies [CITATION_1] .",
